        <abstract> 
<p>Mentions American edition of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p>  
<p>A "savage" review [by John Duns] in <hi rend="italic">North British Review</hi> [32 (1860): 455–68].</p> 
            <p>Comments on views of G. H. K. Thwaites on the survival of simple forms as a problem in his theory.</p>
            <p>Mentions imperfection of geological record.</p>
            <p>Marine origin of coal.</p>
            <p>Illness of Etty.</p> 
<p>Encloses article by Isidore Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire on hare–rabbit crosses [<hi rend="italic">Histoire naturelle générale</hi> (1854–62) 3: 222].</p> 
        </abstract>
